到底为什么？

193
00:07:54,440 --> 00:07:56,160
Why on earth?
到底为什么？

194
00:07:56,160 --> 00:07:57,160
Why on earth?
到底为什么？

195
00:07:57,160 --> 00:07:58,960
This is like a saying.
这像是一个说法。

196
00:07:58,960 --> 00:07:59,960
Yeah.
是的。

197
00:07:59,960 --> 00:08:00,960
Expression.
表达方式。

198
00:08:00,960 --> 00:08:01,960
You can use it in a lot of different ways.
你可以在很多不同的场合使用它。

199
00:08:01,960 --> 00:08:03,600
So we've got some examples for you.
我们给你准备了一些例子。

200
00:08:03,600 --> 00:08:05,680
Let's listen.
我们来听一下。

201
00:08:05,680 --> 00:08:06,680
Example one.
例子一。

202
00:08:06,680 --> 00:08:14,760
Where on earth is my phone?
我的手机到底在哪儿？

203
00:08:14,760 --> 00:08:18,640
Example two.
例子二。

204
00:08:18,640 --> 00:08:26,480
How on earth did you learn English in one month?
你到底是怎么在一个月内学会英语的？

205
00:08:26,480 --> 00:08:30,200
Example three.
例子三。

206
00:08:30,200 --> 00:08:35,560
What on earth is it?
这到底是什么东西？

207
00:08:35,560 --> 00:08:40,840
So when you ask a question with on earth, so why on earth, how on earth, what on earth,
所以当你用 on earth 提问时，比如 why on earth、how on earth、what on earth，

208
00:08:40,840 --> 00:08:42,480
it's like you're showing a lot of surprise.
就像是在表达你非常惊讶。

209
00:08:42,480 --> 00:08:43,480
Okay.
好的。

210
00:08:43,480 --> 00:08:44,480
Great stuff.
太棒了。

211
00:08:44,480 --> 00:08:48,120
So let's just listen to our dialogue a third time.
那我们再听一遍对话吧。

212
00:08:48,120 --> 00:08:55,280
Oh, Armand, thank you for such a thoughtful invitation.
哦，阿曼德，谢谢你这么贴心的邀请。

213
00:08:55,280 --> 00:08:58,840
It's really very nice of you to invite us over for dinner.
你邀请我们过来吃晚饭真是太好了。

214
00:08:58,840 --> 00:08:59,840
Don't you think so, Ellen?
你不觉得吗，艾伦？

215
00:08:59,840 --> 00:09:00,840
Oh, yes, of course.
哦，是的，当然。

216
00:09:00,840 --> 00:09:01,840
We'd love to come over.
我们很乐意过来。

217
00:09:01,840 --> 00:09:02,840
Can I bring anything?
我需要带点什么吗？

218
00:09:02,840 --> 00:09:03,840
No.
不用。

219
00:09:03,840 --> 00:09:07,280
Don't worry about it.
别担心。

220
00:09:07,280 --> 00:09:10,960
I'll take care of everything.
我会搞定一切的。

221
00:09:10,960 --> 00:09:11,960
I'll see you tonight.
今晚见。

222
00:09:11,960 --> 00:09:12,960
Come with an appetite.
留着胃口来。

223
00:09:12,960 --> 00:09:13,960
I know I will.
我知道我会的。

224
00:09:13,960 --> 00:09:22,160
I don't want to go over to his place for dinner.
我不想去他家吃晚饭。

225
00:09:22,160 --> 00:09:23,160
He gives me the creeps.
他让我起鸡皮疙瘩。

226
00:09:23,160 --> 00:09:26,080
Why on earth did you accept?
你到底为什么要答应？

227
00:09:26,080 --> 00:09:27,080
Come on, Ellen.
拜托，艾伦。

228
00:09:27,080 --> 00:09:28,840
It'll be nice to get to know him.
认识一下他也挺好的。

229
00:09:28,840 --> 00:09:31,180
Besides, he's new to the neighborhood.
再说，他是新搬来的邻居。

230
00:09:31,180 --> 00:09:34,080
He'll be rude to decline his invitation.
拒绝他的邀请会很失礼。

231
00:09:34,080 --> 00:09:35,080
I guess so.
我想是吧。

232
00:09:35,080 --> 00:09:44,000
You always wrote me into things like this.
你总是把我拖进这种事情里。

233
00:09:44,000 --> 00:09:56,280
Ladies.
女士们。

234
00:09:56,280 --> 00:09:57,400
Thank you for coming.
谢谢你们的光临。

235
00:09:57,400 --> 00:09:58,400
You look delicious.
你看起来很好吃。

236
00:09:58,400 --> 00:10:00,400
I mean, beautiful.
我是说，很漂亮。

237
00:10:00,400 --> 00:10:01,400
Please come in.
请进。

238
00:10:01,400 --> 00:10:02,400
Oh, Arlond, you are too kind.
哦，阿隆德，你太客气了。

239
00:10:02,400 --> 00:10:23,320
How did I get myself into this?
我怎么把自己搞成这样了？

240
00:10:23,320 --> 00:10:26,120
We want to know what you think happens next.
我们想知道你觉得接下来会发生什么。

241
00:10:26,120 --> 00:10:29,360
Yes, what happens in this dialogue next.
是的，这个对话接下来会发生什么。

242
00:10:29,360 --> 00:10:34,520
So we want you to send us your idea of what happens next and we're going to choose the
所以我们希望你把接下来发生的故事想法发给我们，我们会选出

243
00:10:34,520 --> 00:10:35,520
best one.
最好的一个。

244
00:10:35,520 --> 00:10:36,520
That's right.
没错。

245
00:10:36,520 --> 00:10:42,980
Marco and I will choose the best continuation of the story and we'll use that in part three
马可和我会选出故事的最佳续写，然后我们会把它用在《小镇新人》的第三部分。

246
00:10:42,980 --> 00:10:44,680
of The New Guy in Town.
《小镇新人》的第三部分。

247
00:10:44,680 --> 00:10:45,680
That's right.
没错。

248
00:10:45,680 --> 00:10:48,000
So you can give it any direction you want.
所以你可以朝任何方向发挥。

249
00:10:48,000 --> 00:10:49,080
That's right.
没错。

250
00:10:49,080 --> 00:10:53,400
And of course, we'll publish the name of the author with the lesson.
当然，我们会把作者的名字和课程一起发布。

251
00:10:53,400 --> 00:10:54,400
Yes.
是的。

252
00:10:54,400 --> 00:10:59,080
I'm really anxious to see what ideas come up and how we can end this dialogue.
我真的很期待看到大家会有什么想法，以及我们如何结束这个对话。

253
00:10:59,080 --> 00:11:00,080
I know.
我知道。

254
00:11:00,080 --> 00:11:01,760
We've got a lot of really creative users out there.
我们有很多非常有创意的用户。

255
00:11:01,760 --> 00:11:04,120
So I'm really looking forward to this.
所以我真的很期待。

256
00:11:04,120 --> 00:11:05,120
That's right.
没错。

257
00:11:05,120 --> 00:11:06,120
That's right.
没错。

258
00:11:06,120 --> 00:11:09,360
So be sure to send us your ideas, either a private message or you can post it on the
所以一定要把你的想法发给我们，可以私信，也可以发在这节课的

259
00:11:09,360 --> 00:11:12,000
comment section of this lesson.
评论区。

260
00:11:12,000 --> 00:11:16,440
And any other questions or doubts, go to EnglishPod.com and you can leave them there.
如果有其他问题或疑问，请访问EnglishPod.com，你可以在那里留言。

261
00:11:16,440 --> 00:11:17,440
Yes.
是的。

262
00:11:17,440 --> 00:11:19,240
Marco and I are always happy to answer your questions.
马可和我总是很乐意回答你们的问题。

263
00:11:19,240 --> 00:11:20,320
Okay, folks.
好了，各位。

264
00:11:20,320 --> 00:11:29,800
So until then, it's goodbye.
那么，下次再见。
